1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
AI agents are shipping to production faster than any prior software category —

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:15,000
but the testing discipline traditional software earned over decades hasn't caught up.

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:21,000
This is AgentClinic. Every finding bound to evidence in the trace,

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:27,000
every result published natively into UiPath Test Cloud as the system of record.

5
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Coach, not surveillance. Five minutes. Here's how it works.

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:40,000
This agent retried the same broken deploy four times. State hash unchanged,

7
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:48,000
no error log read in between. Seven thousand four hundred tokens, wasted.

8
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:58,000
A general-purpose LLM can describe this trace, but it can't tell you which event drove the verdict,

9
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:03,000
or verify its own claim.

10
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:15,000
What we need is an audit trail — and it needs to live in the release-gate system the team already uses.

11
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:25,000
Seven deterministic detectors, source-controlled.

12
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Every finding must point at specific trace events as evidence —

13
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:45,000
a finding without an evidence span is a contract violation, rejected at the schema layer.

14
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:55,000
The score is reproducible: same trace, same rules, same number, every time.

15
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Section five is the iron rule that matters most. When data is missing, we say so.

16
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:15,000
No guessing. No hallucination. The report admits exactly what it cannot judge —

17
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:30,000
that's how a clinic differs from a courtroom.

18
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Same agent, this time triggered from Automation Cloud.

19
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Same pipeline as the local runtime, but now writing the result straight into Test Manager.

20
00:02:50,000 --> 00:03:00,000
One Test Case per pattern, reusable across runs.

21
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:10,000
One Test Set, one Execution per publish.

22
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:20,000
A per-pattern log with the evidence-bound reason visible right in the dialog the reviewer already uses.

23
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:25,000
The full markdown report attached.

24
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Quality is no longer a late-stage checkpoint.

25
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:35,000
It's a continuous, governed capability — exactly the shape Track 3 is asking for.

26
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:42,000
Four roles, no overlap.

27
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:50,000
Judge is deterministic — the LLM cannot revise the verdict.

28
00:03:50,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Coach rides UiPath's AgentHub LLM Gateway, so every LLM call stays inside the AI Trust Layer

29
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:05,000
for audit and PII redaction. No direct LLM provider API key.

30
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:10,000
Test Cloud is the system of record.

31
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:15,000
UiPath is the orchestration and governance layer that ties everything together.

32
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:25,000
The whole codebase was written by Claude Code over eleven days.

33
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:32,000
Every commit visible in the git log.

34
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:38,000
Repository public, MIT licensed, CI green, error matrix documented.

35
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:42,000
Drop a trace in, get an audit trail.

36
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Thank you.
